en_223418_0	The head of the terrorist who attacked the Zion Church on Easter Sunday, presently buried in the Kalliyankadu Hindu cemetery in Batticaloa is to be exhumed today.
en_223418_1	This is according to an order given by the Batticaloa Magistrate's Court.
en_223418_2	The order was given after the Criminal Investigations Department made submissions to the Batticaloa Magistrate's Court on Friday.
en_223418_3	Accordingly, the Batticaloa District Secretary has been ordered to exhume the remains of the terrorist from the present burial site and to identify a specific location suitable for burial.
en_223418_4	The court issued the order following the protest in the last couple of days against the burial of the remains of the attacker of the Zion Church in the Kalliyankadu Hindu cemetery in Batticaloa.
